p.-text An avatar is a graphical representation of the user. It can be build from a photo, an icon or one or two letters.

h3 Using avatars

p.-text
  | To render an avatar, use the class <code>a-avatar</code> in a div element and put an image inside. The image
  | must be square in order not to be stretched.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    div(class=`a-avatar`)
      img(src='../../assets/images/person-s.jpg')(alt="avatar")
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-avatar">
      <img src="path/to/image.jpg">
    </div>

h3 Using icons as avatars

p.-text
  | You can use an avatarized version of the <a href="../icon/">Chi icons library</a>. Just include the
  | <code>a-avatar</code> to the icon container.
ul#a-tabs--icons.a-tabs
  li.-active
    a(href="#iconsSVG") SVG
  li
    a(href="#iconsWebFont") Web Font
.example.-mb3
  #iconsSVG.a-tabs-panel.-active
    .-p3
      .a-grid
        each icon in iconExamples
          .a-col.-w1
            div(class="a-icon a-avatar")
              svg
                use(xlink:href=`#icon-${icon}`)
    :code(lang="html")
      <div class="a-icon a-avatar">
        <svg>
          <use xlink:href="#icon-user"></use>
        </svg>
      </div>

  #iconsWebFont.a-tabs-panel
    .-p3
      .a-grid
        each icon in iconExamples
          .a-col.-w1
            div(class="a-avatar")
              i(class=`a-icon icon-${icon}`)
    :code(lang="html")
      <div class="a-avatar">
        <i class="a-icon icon-user"></i>
      </div>

h3 Using letters as avatars

p.-text
  | Where there is not an available photograph for the user, use one or two letters to create one. Use the
  | <code>-textUppercase</code> text utility class to render badges in all uppercase. <code>-textLowercase</code> and
  | <code>-textCapitalized</code> are also supported.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3.a-grid
    .a-col.-w1
      div(class=`a-avatar`) AA
    .a-col.-w1
      div(class=`a-avatar`) M
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-avatar">AA</div>

